cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software, the OpenAPI specification it implements,
  or the methodology described in the companion papers, please cite
  the appropriate artifact(s) below. The Costryx three-layer IP
  architecture (Paper → Software → API Contract) is anchored by
  permanent Zenodo DOIs and protected by USPTO / TIPO / PCT filings.

# ──────────────────── PRIMARY ARTIFACT (this repository) ─────────────────────
type: software
title: "costryx-leq-extractor"
abstract: >-
  Reference implementation of the Equivalent Spatial Length (Leq) metrology
  framework for sub-THz interconnects (1.6 T – 3.2 T), including PCIe 8.0
  PAM4 256 GT/s channel validation under a fixed reference plane. Provides
  the executable counterpart (Layer 2) of the Costryx three-layer IP
  architecture.
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-05-25"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.20384916"
url: "https://github.com/costryx/costryx-leq-extractor"
repository-code: "https://github.com/costryx/costryx-leq-extractor"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - signal integrity
  - sub-THz interconnect
  - equivalent spatial length
  - Leq metrology
  - PCIe 8.0
  - PAM4
  - SerDes
  - SHA-256
  - NIST FIPS PUB 180-4
  - JCGM 100:2008
  - ISO IEC 17025
  - audit trail
  - hash chain
  - MHL manifest
  - three-anchor decision rule

authors:
  - family-names: Hsu
    given-names: Chin-Yu
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0009-6267-7897"
    affiliation: "Independent Researcher"
    email: "chinyu@costryx.net"

