# ─────────────────────── ADDITIONAL REFERENCES (Layer 1) ─────────────────────
# Companion academic papers that establish the theoretical foundation.

references:
  - type: report
    title: >-
      256 GT/s PAM4 Channel Validation Under a Fixed Reference Plane —
      Differential-Mode Phase Residual, Analytical Theory of Equivalent
      Spatial Length, and Its Application to Sub-THz Interconnect
      Characterization (V4.0 Working Report)
    year: 2026
    month: 5
    date-released: "2026-05-25"
    doi: "10.5281/zenodo.20382496"
    url: "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20382496"
    license: CC-BY-4.0
    authors:
      - family-names: Hsu
        given-names: Chin-Yu
        orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0009-6267-7897"
        affiliation: "Independent Researcher"
    abstract: >-
      Layer 1 (Paper) of the Costryx three-layer IP architecture. Establishes
      the analytical theory of Equivalent Spatial Length (Leq) for sub-THz
      interconnects under a fixed reference plane, including the PCIe 8.0
      three-anchor (64 / 96 / 128 GHz) decision rule, σ_Leq five-source GUM
      Type A/B uncertainty propagation, and the Measurement Hash Ledger (MHL)
      methodology.

  - type: report
    title: >-
      Equivalent Spatial Length in 1.6 T – 3.2 T Interconnects (V2.4)
    year: 2026
    month: 5
    date-released: "2026-05-24"
    doi: "10.5281/zenodo.20341571"
    url: "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20341571"
    license: CC-BY-4.0
    authors:
      - family-names: Hsu
        given-names: Chin-Yu
        orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0009-6267-7897"
        affiliation: "Independent Researcher"
    abstract: >-
      Foundational working paper (V2.4) introducing the Equivalent Spatial
      Length (Leq) framework for 1.6 T to 3.2 T high-speed interconnects.
      Predecessor to the V4.0 working report and the v0.1.0 reference
      implementation.

